    "updated_at": "2015-01-23T17:27:09Z",
    "body": "Right, but as per the [recent RFC](https://github.com/aturon/rfcs/blob/show-string-guidelines/text/0000-show-string-guidelines.md), the String trait (being renamed to Display) is intended for user-facing output. For users, negative zero makes no sense, as they're unlikely to even be aware of IEEE 754.\n\nThe Show trait (being renamed to Debug) is what's used for debugging, so that _should_ distinguish the two.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
